Good seafood place. I can't count how many times I have ordered from them.
Good food. But they missed a dish for me and called me to come back to get it. It wasted my time.

Best Walnut Shrimp & Singapore Noodles in Chinatown! They keep the sauce for the shrimp separate for take out so they don't get soggy. They give a very good amount, including a bed of broccoli, versus lettuce at other places.
This spot offers amazing service as well as yummy menu. One of my favourite places around town. The food and drinks came out quickly and the prices were affordable. Highly recommended.
Enjoyed the time with my coworkers and the food!
Love everything here! One of my favorite restaurants in Chinatown

They use MSG, but you can ask them not to (except spicy steamed wontons). This is the only place in Chinatown I ever go to anymore. Their Giant Alaskan Crab three ways is an amazing experience, well worth the money.
Foods are delicious and fresh.  Great service

Try their Marinated Beef and Asparagus, as well as their Golden Egg Yolk Pumpkin (although best shared with many people as it is very heavy). This place is probably one of my favorite places for generic authentic Chinese cuisine.  I usually have a hard time giving 5 stars to Chinese places since I cook it at home but this place is pretty solid. All the food is flavorful and they have a good variety of dishes as well. They aren't doing anything new but have good execution on classic Chinese dishes. I'm a big fan of their gold egg yolk anything. They also have a large assortment of seafood options although I've only had the lobster which was pretty similar to other places.  Atmosphere and service are good, but it can get a little loud as tables are close together. They get pretty busy at peak times, so be prepared for a wait.  Overall a great place that is on my list of routine dinner spots, give them a try!
I've been eating in Chinatown for 30 years and had never been in this place. Glad I went. Everything was good, but I had the best clams I've ever eaten. Going back again soon.
Small,no parking,food is fine.
Good

Went during trip to Chicago earlier this year. Took a while for wait staff to come to us, but it was busy. When we were served, everything was on point. Our drinks were never empty, the food was amazing and in GREAT portions. If you live in Chicago, and haven't been, go. You'll enjoy it
Good Cantonese seafood and vegetables.
Service was a little rushed but the food was tasty

Poor seating system, put our name on the list and watched others walk in directly to tables, spots being held for them by people already seated at the tables,  I guess. We waited 45min, the waiter takes us to a table with four empty seats, one occupied by a man.The person already seated at the table (shook his head and said "no, not with me") maybe he did not want to sit with my party which included (African American people) so we were told to get back in line and wait longer for another table while four seats remained unoccupied. We left and spent our money elsewhere.

Waited an hour with my party of four on Christmas. Several people went a head of us and an single guy who just walked in got a table for five. When the waiter approached the table the guy said we would have to wait because he did not want to sit next to us (Black people). Too bad would have got a nice tip.

Amazing food. Top notch service. cannot speak enough praise about this restaurant.
Good seafood... love it. Lobster and jelly fish is the bomb ..

The cantonese style rice crepes are good, and they also have tasty Tai Shan style wonton soup. It'd be better if they can keep a good consistency on their food, and better hygiene needed for the bathrooms.
Great live seafood.  Good service,. All the food was good.
Excellent food!! Easy Chinatown location.  Parking may be a challenge
Fast service

Definitely a regular spot that we hit in our Chinatown rotation from time to time. Note street parking will run ya $2 per hour, and no issues having a meal here and to be in and out within an hour. For food, we did a single order of wonton soup, some pan fried beef noodles (quite nice as it wasn't too greasy!), an order of the mixed seafood and tofu casserole, and some stir fried string beans. For two this people plenty of food, but I have to say I thought it was a great value in terms of portion and quality. In addition to the food being good, I did notice they have quite the selection of bubble teas. Other notable dishes I enjoy here are the egg tofu and the snow pea leaves when they have them available.  Overall I'd say a good value, place is clean, and service isn't bad!  'Til next time!
Great local family style place. Traditional cooking how should be.

The food is well prepared & presented very nice. The seafood is really fresh & they actually know how to properly cook it. We definitely will be frequenting this place more often. Make reservations or be prepared to wait a bit for a table.

I’ve come here for dim sum, which was good.  However, the dinner dishes could improve.  The salt& pepper smelt dish was served soft and in clusters, and lack of flavor (missing the salt & pepper).  It should have been crispy and individual smelts.   The Hong Kong egg plant was saved by all the extra spices, which was flavorful. Otherwise, the egg plant batter was loose and it could have been more flavorful as well.  The salty/ sweet boba drink they advertise... was too sweet.  Presentation of the dishes are good.  They have a bar, but we brought our own wine and they were good with this.  I gave it 4 stars because I believe this restaurant can improve and the waiters are interested in how the dishes tasted.

Food was great! There was use of MSG, but every once in a while, it's really good. All of the food comes in very big portions, especially the Wonton Soup. The soup was very good, and we all wanted seconds on it.  There is a Lazy Susan on the table, and the way we ate all the food was similar to your very own buffet. My favorite item was the Mongolian beef. All the other food was just as good. Would recommend for good Chinese food in big portions in Chinatown. 5/5
The best food I ever had , just a little pricey,  but excellent food :-)
Very Bad service. We ask for Bubble tea and they dindt want to included the bubbles.

Freshest dim sum in Chinatown. No joke
Delicious and friendly staffs, found our new spot for dinner.
The best duck in town and the best fried rice and the best seafood
Food ordered are salty, otherwise are delicious.

I love their food.

Amazing
Excellent food and service!!

This is a gem! Tucked away in old Chinatown this fairly new restaurant is one of my go-to places! The clams are the highlight!!  Pros: Seafood has great value Cons: Waiit time is long (small place) and lack of Cantonese might be a handicap  If you are feeling fancy, try the Alaskan King Crab. Costly but good

The Establishment was very pleasantly set up with good lighting and fresh white napkins and tablecloths. The Restrooms were very well maintained. The restaraunt didnt have any foul smells like some other places in Chinatown we've been to. We ordered Crab Rangoon & Potstickers for Appetizers. My wife loved the Rangoon (I dont eat them)and we both loved the Potstickers, so did our daughter. Our daughter ordered Beef & Asparagus, Wife ordered Beef w/garlic & onions and I had the honey walnut shrimp. Asian food is on the top of our list as Latin food is also. These potstickers were simply amazing and made my mouth water with every bite. I couldve made a meal out of them alone. All 3 of us agreed that was the best meal we've EVER had in Chinatown. We will be back there again promise that
No bad experiences.

This was the busiest restaurant we saw in Chinatown. It was for good reason. The food was fantastic. The menu had so many authentic dishes I've never heard of or even imagined existed. So, we tried several dishes. They were all great. We had a great experience here.
Be prepared for very odd food choices if you aren't used to Chinese and maybe even if you are

username: Mad Science of Chicago's Western Suburbs

caption: The food is average and has tons of MSG added. The service needs to be improved.

Get any of the seafood here! Salt and pepper smelt is amazing! Mushroom noodle was just OK, but why get mushroom at a seafood place? Mapo togu was good but spicy (ask without meat). Pea pods in sauce was amazing! Third visit in 2 days! Normal pea pods weren't as good. Getting lobster at a good price!

The fried smelt was very good! Mushroom and shrimp crepe was ok. The pea pod with scallops, mapo tofu, and jelly fish were delicious!!! We came here 3 times within 2 days just because everything was so good!
Delicious! Plain and simple. Try the burger and lobster brunch combo if you are really hungry. Both are equally as good.
Great food and amazing service. Was here with a party of nine and we all had a great fun time. Great variety of food options and the time it took was quick.
Feels like home

Best Cantonese restaurant in Chicago Chinatown authentic Hong Kong style and taste you'll have to try their milk tea the best.
Yummy seafood and traditional Chinese. Quick service , usually no waiting.
So much good food here! Must try yum cha here in the morning! Congee n wontons! The sea salt coffee with foam! The pork crepes!!so yum yum 😋

Excellent food, adequate level of service, and pleasant atmosphere at reasonable price. I had Lobster with ginger, spring onion, and soft noodles, also steamed greens with oyster sauce . It was quite good, but I would have been glad for a little more seasoning on the noodles. I'll eat here again, for sure.
Food very tasty and not too salty

Great

Stumble around this restaurant in Chinatown. To my surprise.  The food was amazing and service was outstanding!  Would highly recommend this restaurant in a heart beat. One of the best tasing restaurant in Chinatown.
Authentic Hong Kong Seafood house. Byo. Nice owners. Casual. Open late

Great food and service.  We ordered king crab in scallion ginger, hand shredded chk, fish fillet with tofu and veggie, shredded port chow mein, snow pea tips, clams in black bean sauce, and steamed oysters in black bean sauce.  Everything was great.  Seafood was fresh.  Restaurant is clean.  Service fast and polite...in chinatown!!!  Our family really enjoyed it.  It is a small restaurant, i would guess 3 big tables and 9 smaller ones, so maybe plan to go early or call ahead
Surprisingly good spot...great food and you can byob!!!
Food was decent...service could be friendlier.
Great Food and good price. Shrimp salt and pepper was amazing and the sweet and sour was amazing. Best in Chicago
Very fresh and delicious. Best pot stickers, they are huge and full of meat. Recommend.

Food was delicious and seafood was quite fresh. The steamed giant crabs with vermicelli noodles was very good. One thing to keep in mind, it's a pretty big serving (see pic). The Bitter Melon Fried in Salted Egg Yolk was tasty, but it feels heavy after a bit.
Probably the most authentic food have come across.  Has become my new favorite spot since my other place closed down.
Great food and friendly services

Excellent service, a lot of servers working hard. (Please tip them well) Dining area is bright, clean, modern but a bit tight. Dishes were served within 10min. after order. Food was very fresh, perfectly done, not too salty, and reasonably priced. Food is a bit oily but expected for restaurant; just request less. Will return for sure; discount for cash pay too, just remember to ask server
their wantons lunch special are my favorite!!!

Came here during lunch so the breakfast menu, lunch specials, and the full menu were all available. This place has been open since Jan 2018. Tea and ice water were immediately delivered to the table. Service was great and they were accommodating to substitutions. Food was fresh, delicious, and made-to-order. Highly recommend the milk tea, congee, rice crepe rolls and any of the seafood.
The food is decent granted it is just opened. Give it time. It will get better. They offer us 10% for paying cash.
The best food and servers really helpful. So i recommend for this restaurant

Absolutely delicious! We ordered the spicy crab special, the seafood and pork fried rice, and seafood and vegetable stir fry. Everything was fantastic; the waiters were attentive, the restaurant was packed, all of the dishes we tried were very flavorful and perfectly cooked.
This restaurant isn't that good. The food here is ok but could be better. I asked for a sprite, but instead they gave a broken coke . Please make the service better!
Good food and reasonably priced. Go for the breakfast specials. The milk tea is good... But ask for less sugar as it's a bit too sweet.

Great milk tea drinks!! One of the best in Chinatown. I tried their sea salt milk tea and hazelnut chocolate milk tea. It has a creamy richness to it that reminds me of boba guys in NYC. It's also not overly sweet, which I like. The food is classic Cantonese food. Delicious. Their casseroles are very flavorful and cooked with a strong flame -- which does wonders for tender seafoods and the authentic Cantonese food taste. Great service as well. I wish they had movie nights on their projector because it's huge!
